            <c02 level="item" id="d1e197">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>George Ripley</persname>to Rev. Dr. 
                  <persname>[Convers] Francis</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1846 Dec 9</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>1 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Responds to a note of thanks from Francis;
                  expresses appreciation for the "friendly acts since
                  my first students life at 
                  <geogname>Cambridge</geogname>"; expresses
                  gratification that his books can give pleasure to
                  others.]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e222">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>George Ripley</persname>to 
                  <persname>Charles J. Jones</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1873 Oct 8</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>1 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[States that he has not seen Mr. Reid, but feels
                  sure the proposed date, November 1, will be
                  agreeable.]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e244">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>George Ripley</persname>to Dear
                  Madam</unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1878 Apr 19</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>2 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Advises her to delay offering her manuscript for
                  publication until later in the year as everyone in
                  the trade is "on the wing" during the summer;
                  recommends contacting 
                  <corpname>Harper Bros.</corpname>, 
                  <corpname>Charles Scribner &amp; Sons</corpname>, and
                  <corpname>George P. Putnam, Sons</corpname>in
                  August.]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
         </c01>
